node.text: In this video, I talk about how to listen without giving feedback and I answer a few Q&A’s.

node.title: Listening Without Offering Feedback and Q&A

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 05, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A little secret from a therapist: Burnout is not a symbol of how hardworking, nice, or productive you are. Running yourself to the ground is not a way to show people how much you care. Burnout is a sign of unhealthy perimeters with yourself and others. Repeat After Me: Me: Overextending myself is not healthy for me. It's beneficial for me to have limits with myself and others. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Burnout is an indicator of unhealthy perimeters around your time and energy. 

#nedranuggets #setboundariesfindpeace

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Perhaps people aren't bougie, funny acting, or standoffish; instead, they might be introverted, living differently than you, or enjoying their own world. You will not understand everything about other people. And when you don't understand attempt to learn more without judging. Judgment is most prevalent when we think other people should be like us. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Embrace people being different by not judging their differences negatively. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Remember This: Endings don't require drama or toxic behaviors. You can end something because it's not what you want, it doesn't fit where you're going, you're tired of trying to make it work, your needs have changed, or you can no longer accept what is happening You don't have to wait for a major offense to let things go. It's okay to bow out gracefully. Sometimes peace is more important than giving someone a piece of your mind. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
It's possible to gently let go. ⁣⁣⁣

Go in peace. 
⁣
{Soft Endings}⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣#nedranuggets ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
Forgiveness is a choice you make, and it doesn't require you to return to unhealthy situations. If the situation, the person, or you have not changed, you will be returning to an unhealthy situation. 

Change is the highest form of apology and also a reason to forgive and return. 

“Just because someone is sorry does not mean they have changed.” ~Dr. Henry Cloud 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I knew I was maturing when I realized: @NEDRATAWWAB Many of the issues that had in my relationships were the result of unhealthy boundaries. It wasn't my job to rescue people and meddle in their problems. Gossiping is not the only way to connect in conversation. Some people won't change in a time frame that works for what I want for my life. I was getting upset with people for being themselves (I was expecting something different from people who hadn't changed.) Asking for help is healthy, not weak. There are some things that may not get over. www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
When presented with helpful information, maturity is changing your perspective, adhering to the life lessons you've learned through trial and error, and growing from watching others. Also, maturity is embodying your beliefs. 

How have you noticed yourself maturing? 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'There There is still time to tell your kids: "I did not have the proper tools, and I apologize that you didn't get what you needed." "I love you." "Your opinion matters to me." "I made a mistake." "I'm listening. Please tell me how you feel." "I am here for you; please tell me what you need." "I'm proud of you." "I don't know. Let's find out together." "I wasn't listening then, but am listening now." "I'm sorry." "My behavior wasn't okay." @NEDRATAWWAB www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
Relationships can be salvaged and repaired when people are accountable and willing to change. ⁣

Whether children are under 18 years old, or adults, they benefit from an apology, words of affirmation, and changed behavior. 

⁣
#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Using social media becomes easier when @NEDRATAWWAE you: Manage your page and not everyone else's (you can't determine what other people post) Shape your experience (unfollow, block, mute, and delete) Understand that the people you follow won't always get it right Assume less about people Gently approach topics that need to be addressed (How would speak about this in person?) Address the underlying reasons why you're being triggered Set perimeters around how and when you use it www.nedralawwab.com'.

node.text:
Social media can be helpful, or it can be harmful. Perhaps, your experience is shaped by the community you create and the ideas that you nurture. 

True enough, social media is setup up to keep you coming back. That said, you determine what you're returning to over and over.  You have the opportunity to choose what you want to experience in this space. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says '6 THINGS THAT ARE ENTIRELY NORMAL @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
What’s normal is what’s typical. 
 
Conversely, what’s normal may not be what’s best, and it might be healthier for you to change your perspective.  
 
#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says '6 THINGS THAT ARE ENTIRELY NORMAL @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'It's norma normal to question whether you're making the right decision. Often you learn that you made a mistake only after making a decision that didn't work in your favor. Continue to take cannes and know that you won't always choose the perfect option. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'It's normal to repeat the same mistakes in relationships. Sometimes it takes a while to become conscious of your power to change situations. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'It's normal to argue to be right. Of course, you want to be understood, but some people will not understand you no matter how loud you talk or how many bullet points you have. It takes a while to figure out that you can't change how someone chooses to think. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 30, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'It's normal to have needs. All humans have needs, and it's healthy to express your needs. However, there will be some people who cannot meet your needs. It doesn't mean that you need to pretend to he without needs. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'It's normal to think that you have to do the most. Many of us are trained to be productive (busy). When you aren't productive, it is translated as lazy. Redefine what it means to be productive by including rest in your definition. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'It's normal to want to change people. It's so much easier for other people to change than for you to try a different approach, change yourself, accep things as they are, or move on. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 29, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I knew I was growing when I started to empathize with people who encouraged me to stay in unhealthy situations. To them, this was the best they (I) could do. They weren't ready to leave unhealthy conditions, so they spread fear instead. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Sometimes others people's response to your decisions is not about you. 

Empathy, where there was known before, is a sign of growth.

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'This is not being nice; it's people-pleasing: pleasing: @NEDRATAWWAB Accepting blame to keep the peace Operating beyond your capacity Disregarding your needs Allowing people who haven't changed back into your life Doing for others what they could do for themselves (enabling) Going out of the way to accommodate people Being passive Remaining silent when you have an issue www.nedralawwab.com'.

node.text:
{People-pleasing is not kindness.}

Living to make others happy often leaves you unhappy. People-pleasing is rooted in not feeling worthy of love, fearing rejection, or unhealthy self-esteem. 

You can be in a healthy relationship with others AND take care of yourself. 
Healthy people want you to be able to be happy and healthy. 

You are not kind to yourself when you neglect your needs for the needs of others. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 25, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A little secret from a therapist: When you are assertive, people might call you mean or combative. It's easier for the other person when you are passive. Some people don't want you to have an opinion, make a different decision than them, or even tell them you're not okay with something. The mere fact that you have a boundary or different view can be offensive even when you speak politely. Repeat After Me: I can be polite, but I don't need to be quiet. I can be assertive and know that someone might still be offended. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
You can be polite, and it might still be perceived as mean. Some things need to be said or done that others may find offensive. For example, there's no easy way to say, "Thank you for this opportunity. This situation is no longer working for me." If someone disagrees with you, they will likely be hurt and offended. However, it can still be healthier for you to leave. 

Things are complicated, and perhaps there's no easy way to be assertive. 

#nedranuggets
